f that is a must then I guess I will have to find another way or forget about caching altogether.</p>\n<p>Also if you need a PhD to be able to figure out W3TC settings, then I think it is just not worth it...\n</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/7qaYNhXj3OY\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:141:\"http://wordpress.org/support/topic/plugin-w3-total-cache-installation-on-30-multisite-wordpress-mu-domain-mapping-on-shared-host#post-1744583\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:11;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"kkropp on \"Minifying JS without losing JS-related functionality in blog templates\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:151:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/SAmfrhSRdBA/plugin-w3-total-cache-minifying-js-without-losing-js-related-functionality-in-blog-templates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Sun, 17 Oct 2010 21:21:03 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"1744403@http://wordpress.org/support/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1502:\"<p>Hello-</p>\n<p>We\'ve been very, very impressed with this plugin so far, but have been unable to deal with one particular issue. However, we think we\'ve isolated the cause. \"Minifying\" (a word we didn\'t even know yesterday…) java scripts seems to break pages generated by the archive.php template in our theme, iThemes Builder (the one we use to generate our blog).</p>\n<p>Here are the symptoms: When we enable the W3 Total Cache feature that minifies selected java scripts, everything works perfectly in our individual pages and posts. However, none of the js-related functionality works in our blog pages when we access them. When we disable the W3 Total Cache feature that minifies js, the issue goes away–all the js-related functionality is back. The plugin and the caching is still active, but the minifying is no longer happening.</p>\n<p>Here\'s what we\'re trying to accomplish: We\'d like to continue using the feature that minifies js as much as possible on the site, since it seems to very meaningfully reduce HTTP requests (the difference between an \"A\" and an \"F\" in YSlow) on our pages and posts. This is a good thing for our shared hosting environment with HostGator. However, we\'d like to disable the feature for pages generated by archive.php so that our blog page isn\'t broken.</p>\n<p>Any ideas out there about how we might do that most effectively?</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance,<br />\nKarl\n</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/SAmfrhSRdBA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:140:\"http://wordpress.org/support/topic/plugin-w3-total-cache-minifying-js-without-losing-js-related-functionality-in-blog-templates#post-1744403\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:12;