e-path-found-in-the-database-is-inconsistent-with-the-current-paths\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Sun, 17 Oct 2010 02:00:10 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"1743258@http://wordpress.org/support/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:783:\"<p>Hi, i try to use w3tc plugin, but have a issue.</p>\n<p>Firstly, I tried to use subdomain as a cache disk (with no results). Today I signed up for s3 amazon and continue receive this message:</p>\n<blockquote><p>\"The path found in the database (wp-content/uploads) is inconsistent with the current paths found on your server. Please manually adjust the upload path either in miscellaneous settings or in the site\'s edit page if in network mode.\"</p></blockquote>\n<p>Could you please advise what am I doing wrong?</p>\n<p>Thank you</p>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/w3-total-cache/\">http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/w3-total-cache/</a>\n</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/ul-x6CYgXO0\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:139:\"http://wordpress.org/support/topic/plugin-w3-total-cache-the-path-found-in-the-database-is-inconsistent-with-the-current-paths#post-1743258\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:25;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8: