\"Google-Translate\" src=\"http://ottopress.com/files/2011/06/Google-Translate.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"175\" height=\"175\" />While looking at my backlinks today, I noticed a <a href=\"http://www.photofloue.net/2011/06/01/une-galerie-photo-dans-wordpress/\">site in French</a> had linked to my post about <a title=\"Photo Gallery Primer\" href=\"http://ottopress.com/2011/photo-gallery-primer/\">making photo galleries</a>. He mentioned that the Google Translate wasn&#8217;t great. I took a look, and while I don&#8217;t know how good the text translation was, I did notice that Google strangely tried to translate the code as well, thus screwing it all up.</p>\n<p>A quick search <a href=\"http://translate.google.com/support/\">revealed</a> that all one had to do was to add the &#8220;notranslate&#8221; class to any wrapping object to prevent its contents from being translated.</p>\n<p>Now, I use the <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/syntaxhighlighter/\">Syntax Highligher Evolved</a> plugin to display code on my site (although I use an older version because I like the look and functionality of it better than the latest version). So I edited the plugin and found where it inserts the PRE tag, and added the notranslate class to it. And voila, now my code doesn&#8217;t get translated anymore.</p>\n<p>Just a helpful tip for anybody who posts code on their sites.</p>\n<div class=\"plusone\"><g:plusone size=\"tall\" href=\"http://ottopress.com/2011/google-translation-tip/\"></g:plusone></div><a href=\'http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fotto42.com%2F9k&count=vertical&related=otto42&text=Google%20Translation%20Tip\' class=\'twitter-share-button\' data-text=\'Google Translation Tip\' data-url=\'http://otto42.com/9k\' data-counturl=\'http://ottopress.com/2011/google-translation-tip/\' data-count=\'vertical\' data-via=\'ottodestruct\' data-related=\'otto42\'></a><span class=\"fb_share\"><fb:like href=\"http://ottopress.com/2011/google-translation-tip/\" layout=\"box_count\"></fb:like></span>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"xmlns\";a:7:{s:7:\"content\";s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";s:3:\"wfw\";s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";s:2:\"dc\";s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";s:4:\"atom\";s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";s:2:\"sy\";s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";s:5:\"slash\";s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";s:5:\"media\";s:29:\"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/\";}}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://ottopress.com/2011/google-translation-tip/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"xmlns\";a:7:{s:7:\"content\";s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";s:3:\"wfw\";s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";s:2:\"dc\";s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";s:4:\"atom\";s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";s:2:\"sy\";s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";s:5:\"slash\";s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";s:5:\"media\";s:29:\"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/\";}}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"8\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"xmlns\";a:7:{s:7:\"content\";s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";s:3:\"wfw\";s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";s:2:\"dc\";s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";s:4:\"atom\";s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";s:2:\"sy\";s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";s:5:\"slash\";s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";s:5:\"media\";s:29:\"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/\";}}}}s:29:\"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/\";a:2:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";