57:\"<fb:like href=\'http%3A%2F%2Fottopress.com%2F2011%2Fpost-formats-presentation%2F\' send=\'true\' layout=\'standard\' show_faces=\'true\' width=\'450\' height=\'65\' action=\'recommend\' colorscheme=\'light\' font=\'lucida+grande\'></fb:like><p>Slides for the presentation I gave on Post Formats at the <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/WordPress-Memphis/\">WordPress Memphis Meetup</a> yesterday. It was a short presentation, only about 15-20 minutes, really. Post formats simply aren&#8217;t that complicated, and tend to be easy to grasp quickly.</p>\n<p><iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/present/embed?id=ddb9vs6z_13dq6wvfhp&#038;interval=15&#038;size=m\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"555\" height=\"451\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Link if you can&#8217;t see the embedded version above: <a href=\"http://go.otto42.com/uhwrv\">http://go.otto42.com/uhwrv</a></p>\n<p>I followed up showing on a demo site how you could use CSS to easily add and style post formats. During that, I used the <a href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/web-developer/\">Web Developer Addon</a> for Firefox, since that&#8217;s my preferred means of quickly editing CSS files and seeing the results, live. Frankly, I just find Firebug too complicated to use for that sort of thing.</p>\n<div class=\"plusone\"><g:plusone size=\"tall\" href=\"http://ottopress.com/2011/post-formats-presentation/\"></g:plusone></div><a href=\'http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fotto42.com%2F9a&count=vertical&related=otto42&text=Post%20Formats%20Presentation\' class=\'twitter-share-button\' data-text=\'Post Formats Presentation\' data-url=\'http://otto42.com/9a\' data-counturl=\'http://ottopress.com/2011/post-formats-presentation/\' data-count=\'vertical\' data-via=\'ottodestruct\' data-related=\'otto42\'></a><span class=\"fb_share\"><fb:like href=\"http://ottopress.com/2011/post-formats-presentation/\" layout=\"box_count\"></fb:like></span>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explici